# ----- AO / Arweave -----
.ao-cache/
.arweave-cache/
# `aos` CLI auto-creates a wallet JWK at ~/.aos.json on first spawn. That JWK
# is the SOLE controller of every AO process the wallet has ever owned
# (including, as of Phase 6.1, the canonical `xion-core` process). It must
# never appear inside the repo, regardless of which directory it is copied
# into. The `**/wallet*.json` line above does NOT cover the literal name
# `.aos.json`, so it is enumerated explicitly here.
.aos.json
**/.aos.json
*.aos.json
# Defense-in-depth: any file whose name contains "jwk" is treated as a key.
# Arweave wallets are always JWKs; this catches `arweave-keyfile-*.json`,
# `wallet.jwk.json`, and similar.
*.jwk
*.jwk.json
**/*.jwk

