# ----- distributables that are reproducible from source -----
.dist/
release/

# ----- runtime ledger artifacts (orchestrator writes these at repo root by default) -----
# These are append-only hash-chained logs emitted by a running orchestrator
# (Supervisor ticks, Arbiter verdicts, Relay request records, payment commits).
# They are deployment-specific runtime state, not committable doctrine. An
# operator who genuinely wants to snapshot a specific run for audit uses
# `git add -f` explicitly. Default posture is: never pollute the checkout.
SENSORIUM_LEDGER.jsonl
SAFETY_LEDGER.jsonl
SAFETY_LEDGER_ANCHORS.jsonl
REQUEST_LEDGER.jsonl
PAYMENT_LEDGER.jsonl
RESEARCH_SPEND_LEDGER.jsonl

# Broker state files written by the Phase 5g+ SqliteBroker when an operator
# sets XION_BROKER_DB_PATH. SQLite-WAL posture means two sidecar files exist
# alongside the main DB while the broker is live. Never committable.
broker.sqlite3
broker.sqlite3-wal
broker.sqlite3-shm
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite3-wal
*.sqlite3-shm
